Call Abilities

At crystal strength 75, it is possible to learn a crystal strength call ability.
Call abilities may be set on the Party screen by dragging one over from the Call tab to a party member.

*Both characters must be of at least crystal strength level 75.
*Call abilities cannot be set to or from friends' support characters.
*It is not possible to embark on a quest with overlapping call ability characters in the party.

When using a call ability, the called character will trade places with the calling party member. After the ability is triggered, the original character will immediately return to the party.

Additionally, certain call abilities will grant the calling party member special effects.

*The called character's gear, passive abilities, and stats will be reflected in his or her call ability.
*Call abilities that affect the party include the called character as a party member; in other words, the party will be considered to consist of up to four targets.
*Call abilities have an instant turn rate and will not add to the total turn count. They do, however, consume turns during summoning and support.
*Call abilities do not add to the recast gauge of EX abilities.
*Effects that restore or preserve ability use counts do not apply to call abilities.
*If the same special effect is triggered during co-op, the effects do not stack; instead the greater effect will take precedence.
*Call abilities cannot be used during burst mode.
■Enhancing Call Abilities

At crystal strength level 80, a character's call ability will be enhanced.
*The enhancement will be applied automatically. It is not necessary to set the enhancement to the call ability.

■LD Call Abilities

Certain characters can learn LD call abilities from their enhancement boards.

After setting a character who has learned an LD call ability to a party member, you will be able to use in battle both the regular call ability obtained through crystal strength as well as the LD call ability.

The called character will be able to use each of their call abilities once per battle.
Special effects granted by different types of call abilities do not stack, with the newer effect overwriting the older.

More information on obtaining LD call abilities can be found
in the Enhancement Boards guide.
